      "id": "PopularPost343068",
      "post_content": " Awesome. I really love the flavor of this card. I feel that WotC give us a lot of fan-service, and as a player I for one appreciate it greatly. I like finding what I call \"flip-book cards\" where two or more cards with similar effects or synergy have artwork that links them together. This card for example when viewed next to [Worldslayer](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Worldslayer) seems to show a knight shoving the sword into the earth destroying everything in it's wake, or (more likely mechanic-wise) pulling it out again. Thank you WotC.  \n  \nAlso, look at [Wrath of God](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Wrath of God), [Day of Judgment](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Day of Judgment) and [Planar Cleansing](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Planar Cleansing). In that order.",
      "posted_by": "Oxman",
